<bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
<head>Historical Information
</head>
<p>On March 26, 1860 the General Assembly passed an act authorizing the governor to purchase a copy of Joseph Mayo's A GUIDE TO MAGISTRATES: WITH PRACTICAL FORMS FOR THE DISCHARGE OF THEIR DUTIES OUT OF COURT (Richmond: Printed by Colin, Baptist, and Nowlan, 1850) for each justice and county clerk. The auditor of public accounts issued warrants to pay for the copies.
</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
<head>Scope and Content
</head>
<p>These records are part of Auditor of Public Accounts. Disbursements to Localities and Individuals: Local Government Expenses - Clerks. The series consists of receipts signed by Mayo for books purchased from him.
</p>
</scopecontent>
